.SH FILES
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/src\*O - C source files and object files
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/lisp\*O - Lisp source files and compiled files
that define most editing commands.  Some are preloaded;
others are autoloaded from this directory when used.
.\" .PP
.\" /usr/local/emacs/man - sources for the \*LEmacs\*O reference manual.
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/etc\*O - various programs that are used with
GNU Emacs, and some files of information.
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/etc/DOC.*\*O - contains the documentation
strings for the Lisp primitives and preloaded Lisp functions
of GNU Emacs.  They are stored here to reduce the size of
\*LEmacs\*O proper.
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/etc/DIFF\*O discusses GNU Emacs vs. Twenex Emacs;
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/etc/CCADIFF\*O discusses GNU Emacs vs. CCA Emacs;
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/etc/GOSDIFF\*O discusses GNU Emacs vs. Gosling Emacs.
.\" .PP
.\" /usr/local/emacs/etc/SERVICE lists people offering various services
.\" to assist users of GNU Emacs, including education, troubleshooting,
.\" porting and customization.
.PP
These files also have information useful to anyone wishing to write
programs in the \*LEmacs\*O Lisp extension language, which has not yet
been fully documented.
.PP
\*C/usr/lib/emacs/info\*O - files for the Info documentation browser
(a subsystem of \*LEmacs\*O) to refer to.  Currently not much of UNIX
is documented here, but the complete text of the \*LEmacs\*O reference
manual is included in a convenient tree structured form.
.PP
